net.sf.mmm.client.ui.api.widget.complex

Interface UiWidgetAbstractTree.UiTreeModel<NODE>

  • Type Parameters:
    NODE - is the generic type of the tree-nodes of this model.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    UiWidgetAbstractTree.UiTreeModelMutable<NODE>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    UiTreeNodeModel
    Enclosing interface:
    UiWidgetAbstractTree<NODE>

    public static interface UiWidgetAbstractTree.UiTreeModel<NODE>
    This is the interface for the model (adapter) for a UiWidgetTree. If the tree structure should be editable for the end-user you need to implement UiWidgetAbstractTree.UiTreeModelMutable. However, modification of the tree node data is still possible if the tree is editable.

      • getChildren

        List<NODE> getChildren(NODE node)
        This method gets the children of the given tree-node.
        Parameters:
        node - the tree-node for which the children are requested.

        the List of child-nodes or null if NOT available and asynchronous loading is required.

      • getChildrenAsync

        void getChildrenAsync(NODE node,
                      Consumer<List<NODE>> callback)
        This method gets the children of the given tree-node asynchronously.
        Parameters:
        node - the tree-node for which the children are requested.
        callback - is the Consumer that will be called when the children are available. Maybe null if only loading shall be triggered.
